metadata.name: Takashi's Death #356
metadata.description:
Akira by Katsuhiro Otomo.
A global landmark in the shaping of the Cyberpunk genre, and a watershed title for the medium.

I got my hands on the tankōbon(s) more than 20 years ago and those pages upon pages at the end of the third one depicting the destruction of Neo-Tokyo stayed with me ever since. Pages of stunning destruction, leaving me in awe.

This is my generative take on the subject. An attempt to evoke the power of that one panel in a cohesive collection.

Everything procedurally generated at runtime.
You can find more info on the composition here : https://ulucode.com/wp/takashis-death/

Export a PNG capture at various resolutions by pressing the number keys 1 to 9 (top row or numpad, and only in live mode, after pressing "open"). Resolutions ranges from 720 to 7680 pixels ( height ). I recommend starting with "4".

More features are available, but a decent GPU is recommended:
- Press "space" to toggle an animation on/off
- Press "u" to Unlock the camera. You can then :
. Mouse left : Rotate
. Mouse middle/wheel : Zoom
. Mouse right : Translate
. "r" : reset camera
. "a" : change antialiasing quality : 3 settings in rotation. Try this if your framerate is too low.

metadata.name: 7VV1N5 #447
metadata.description:
GO BIG OR GO HOME.

After a week of minimalism code, our hero, the handsome artist Daniel, decided he needed something involving maximalism to reset the balance. Finding pairs to put together is satisfying.

Images will take 6-9 seconds to display and refresh between window resizing.

Use the z key or single click/tap to switch to "zoom" mode, which zooms in and fills the viewport; use z & tap/click to cycle through views. Use x and double-click/tap to go back to square mode.

Note: It doesn't work on Internet Explorer, because Microsoft. iOS is faster than Android.

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

z, click, tap - Switch to & cycle "zoom" mode
x, double-click, double-tap - Switch back out of "zoom" mode.
h - Toggle high-res (slow)
s - Download and save image (takes a few seconds, longer for high-res)

metadata.description:

These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.

metadata.name: Gestalt #228
metadata.description:
"Gestalt" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022

A flurry of many elements derived from my past (and future) strewn across a single canvas. As random as things seem, collectively time tends to reveal hints of order in the chaos. Sometimes, more is more.

Controls:
• Left-click/tap reassembles the piece with one less element each time
• 'R' reassembles the piece with all elements
• 'S' saves the output

“𝚃𝚑𝚎 𝚠𝚑𝚘𝚕𝚎 𝚒𝚜 𝚐𝚛𝚎𝚊𝚝𝚎𝚛 𝚝𝚑𝚊𝚗 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚜𝚞𝚖 𝚘𝚏 𝚒𝚝𝚜 𝚙𝚊𝚛𝚝𝚜.”

Made in p5js
Created May 2022
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: Elswhere Atlas #122
metadata.description:
Trying to navigate through a lucid dream, seeking serenity in chaos.

A generative art series created using noise, math, and p5js.

Keyboard controls:
[S] Save the current view.
[2] Render 2000x3000px image.
[4] Render 4000x6000px image.
[6] Render 6000x9000px image.

Created by Elsif, 2022.06

metadata.name: Microgravity #884
metadata.description:
Microgravity is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022.

Scale symmetry of abstract semiliquid forms.

Click on a section of the image to explore deeper.
- Use keys [0-9] to change the detail level.
- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "R" key to reset the coordinates.

metadata.name: Lost in multidimensional planes #128
metadata.description:
The universe as we know it has three dimensions of space (length, width and depth) and one of time. However, there's the mind-bending possibility that many more dimensions exist out there…
"Lost in multidimensional planes" is an artistic exploration of visualizing 356 in silico created universes with more than 4 dimensions. 

----
- Made entirely with code in p5js.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image.
- Will take several seconds to render, and likely more on mid-range mobile CPUs.
- Tested on Chrome, Brave and Edge.

-	Minters will receive 20% of royalties from the secondary market.
